00:28:58.450 --> 00:29:04.120
but I can say that your last
point about broader engagement

00:29:04.120 --> 00:29:07.279
across different communities,
different organizations,

00:29:07.279 --> 00:29:08.320
is going to be essential.

00:29:08.320 --> 00:29:10.210
If we're thinking
about organizing our--

00:29:10.210 --> 00:29:11.310
let me back up.

00:29:11.310 --> 00:29:13.930
A lot of people have framed
up the climate question,

00:29:13.930 --> 00:29:17.050
many times, as a question
of sort of consumer choice--

00:29:17.050 --> 00:29:18.550
which is very
important, by the way.

00:29:18.550 --> 00:29:22.540
It is important to choose green
energy, do all those things.

00:29:22.540 --> 00:29:24.970
But it cannot be
just consumer choice.

00:29:24.970 --> 00:29:27.790
We have to organize ourselves
to do these transitions

00:29:27.790 --> 00:29:29.472
in a deliberate way.

00:29:29.472 --> 00:29:31.180
And what we all have
right now-- somebody

00:29:31.180 --> 00:29:37.090
earlier in the symposium
used the lovely term

00:29:37.090 --> 00:29:38.830
"find your own tidepool."

00:29:38.830 --> 00:29:43.540
So find your own way to use
the world that you're in,

00:29:43.540 --> 00:29:45.190
use the sphere that you're in.

00:29:45.190 --> 00:29:46.720
Try to think
creatively about what

00:29:46.720 --> 00:29:48.760
can be done within that sphere.

00:29:48.760 --> 00:29:51.700
And it's vitally important to
use those spheres that we're

00:29:51.700 --> 00:29:54.790
already operating in
to maximize how we can

00:29:54.790 --> 00:29:56.030
work with those communities.

00:29:56.030 --> 00:29:58.800
And so the communities of
faith, the communities of--

00:29:58.800 --> 00:30:01.120
I talked about cities,
states, and local governments.

00:30:01.120 --> 00:30:02.830
That's one way to organize,
communities of faith

00:30:02.830 --> 00:30:03.329
is another.

00:30:03.329 --> 00:30:04.675
Universities is another.

00:30:04.675 --> 00:30:06.550
You all can probably
think of many other ways

00:30:06.550 --> 00:30:08.290
to kind of organize ourselves.

00:30:08.290 --> 00:30:10.030
And long ago, the
climate question

00:30:10.030 --> 00:30:12.430
moved from a science
and technology question

00:30:12.430 --> 00:30:15.230
primarily to a question
of ethics, values,

00:30:15.230 --> 00:30:16.930
and social organizing in action.

00:30:16.930 --> 00:30:18.340
And that's where we are today.

00:30:18.340 --> 00:30:20.000
It spans the spectrum.

00:30:20.000 --> 00:30:22.840
And so the question for us is
sort of how do you link those,

00:30:22.840 --> 00:30:25.180
how do you make the links
between all those dimensions?

00:30:25.180 --> 00:30:28.420
And yes, I think making
sure we recognize

00:30:28.420 --> 00:30:30.220
that there are deep
values in what choices

00:30:30.220 --> 00:30:31.970
we're making over the
next couple of years

00:30:31.970 --> 00:30:35.480
is an essential piece
of the answer here.

00:30:35.480 --> 00:30:36.150
- OK.

