you see action that is useful,

00:31:11.260 --> 00:31:14.170
that is moving the needle
on climate change, that

00:31:14.170 --> 00:31:17.980
is geographically,
ethnically, socioeconomically

00:31:17.980 --> 00:31:20.100
diverse and inclusive?

00:31:20.100 --> 00:31:21.110
- It's a great question.

00:31:21.110 --> 00:31:22.632
I don't have a
full answer to it,

00:31:22.632 --> 00:31:24.340
because I think that's
actually something

00:31:24.340 --> 00:31:28.190
that we need creativity and
energy to help us answer

00:31:28.190 --> 00:31:31.690
collectively I do think
that part of the discussion

00:31:31.690 --> 00:31:35.517
here has to focus on, again,
what are the actual benefits?

00:31:35.517 --> 00:31:37.600
What are we actually getting
from this transition?

00:31:37.600 --> 00:31:40.840
We are choosing in this,
I think, a better path.

00:31:40.840 --> 00:31:42.602
We are choosing cleaner air.

00:31:42.602 --> 00:31:43.810
We're choosing better health.

00:31:43.810 --> 00:31:45.820
We're choosing more jobs.

00:31:45.820 --> 00:31:47.890
And those kinds of
discussions are really

00:31:47.890 --> 00:31:49.810
what ought to be
at the core of how

00:31:49.810 --> 00:31:53.230
we discuss amongst ourselves
and discuss much more

00:31:53.230 --> 00:31:56.140
broadly the benefits and
the strategies of doing

00:31:56.140 --> 00:31:57.990
the transition.

00:31:57.990 --> 00:31:59.640
- So here's where
we can go, not just

00:31:59.640 --> 00:32:03.120
we need to eat our vegetables,
about giving things up.

00:32:03.120 --> 00:32:03.720
Excellent.

