The answer is absolutely.

00:32:54.200 --> 00:32:57.180
There's a lot of reasons
to preserve natural areas

00:32:57.180 --> 00:33:01.380
and to kind of encourage
continued growth

00:33:01.380 --> 00:33:03.210
of those natural ecosystems.

00:33:03.210 --> 00:33:05.686
Even in this country,
in the United States,

00:33:05.686 --> 00:33:07.060
partly because of
climate change,

00:33:07.060 --> 00:33:08.643
partly because of
other reasons, we're

00:33:08.643 --> 00:33:11.106
expecting some of, essentially,
the carbon sequestration

00:33:11.106 --> 00:33:13.230
to be tapering off over
the next couple of decades,

00:33:13.230 --> 00:33:15.940
without further kind of
conservation efforts.

00:33:15.940 --> 00:33:17.949
So it's going to be
a key part of it.

00:33:17.949 --> 00:33:19.740
And I think it can
happen in different ways

00:33:19.740 --> 00:33:20.698
in different countries.

00:33:20.698 --> 00:33:23.590
But it's got to be at the
core of how we approach it.

00:33:23.590 --> 00:33:24.380
I agree.

00:33:24.380 --> 00:33:26.590
Yes.

